oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Tooan-Tuh or "Spring Frog"
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Color lithograph portrait of Tooan-Tuh, or "Spring Frog," a Cherokee Chief in a tunic with fringe.
The lithograph is a copy of Charles Bird King's original oil painting of Tooan-Tuh.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:creator: Hoffy, Alfred M., approximately 1790-; King, Charles Bird, 1785-1862
